<p class="">The point was that all the troops engaged in Malaya and Korea should have parcels at concessionary rates. In the case of Korea we could not do that because they had left before the last date of posting. In the case of Malaya the vast majority are in process of having the advantage of these concessionary rates, but there were a number of these men who left this country too late for that purpose and we have decided to allow them to have free parcels.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
